mirabello cavalori (1535â€“1572) was an italian painter of mannerist style, active mainly in florence. cavalori was born in salincorno, near montefortino. he was a contemporary of maso da san friano and younger than vasari. the latter painter employed cavalori in the decoration of the studiolo of francesco i in the palazzo vecchio, for which he produced the wool factory and sacrifice of lavinia (lavinia at the altar) . also in the palazzo vecchio can be found paintings of the blessing of isaac.